---
import Atlas from '@/layouts/Atlas.astro';
import { getInventory, getAllPackages } from '@/lib/atlas';

const inv = await getInventory();
const pkgs = await getAllPackages();
const ch = inv.chapters.find(c => c.id === '05')!;
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');

const sdkCore  = pkgs.find(p => p.id === 'sdk-core')!;
const sdkRs    = pkgs.find(p => p.id === 'sdk-rs')!;
const services = pkgs.find(p => p.id === 'sdk-services')!;
const nodeSdk  = pkgs.find(p => p.id === 'node-sdk')!;
const webSdk   = pkgs.find(p => p.id === 'web-sdk')!;

// Three concrete capability frames for the chain diagram.
const chain = [
  {
    label: 'root · wallet → app',
    space: 'default',
    path: '/',
    actions: ['kv/*', 'sql/*', 'capabilities/*'],
    note: 'signed by the wallet at SIWE time. covers everything the app declared in its manifest.',
  },
  {
    label: 'mid · app → backend',
    space: 'default',
    path: 'reports/',
    actions: ['kv/get', 'kv/put'],
    note: 'subset. narrower path. fewer actions. signed by the app session key.',
  },
  {
    label: 'leaf · backend → worker',
    space: 'default',
    path: 'reports/2026-Q2/',
    actions: ['kv/get'],
    note: 'subset of subset. read-only, single quarter.',
  },
];
---
<Atlas chapter="05" title={ch.title} crumb={`05 · ${ch.title}`}>
  <article class="prose" style="padding: 56px 64px; max-width: 1100px;">
    <div class="label">chapter 05 · {ch.read} · voice: {ch.voice}</div>
    <h1 style="margin-top: 14px;">delegation chains <span class="squig">&amp; ReCap</span></h1>

    <p>
      A TinyCloud delegation is a UCAN-shaped credential that says
      <em>this DID may invoke these actions on these resources, until this
      time, with permission to redelegate (or not).</em> Chains are how
      authority flows: a wallet signs the root, the app session key signs
      a narrower child, the backend signs a narrower grandchild — and
      every link must be a strict subset of its parent.
    </p>

    <p>
      The chain itself is encoded inside a SIWE message as a
      <code>recap</code> resource — a base64url-encoded URN block tucked
      after the <code>Resources:</code> header. <code>parseRecapFromSiwe</code>
      (Rust, exposed through the <a class="pkg-link" href={`${base}/pkg/sdk-rs/`}>{sdkRs.npm}</a>
      WASM seam) extracts the entries; <code>isCapabilitySubset</code> in
      <a class="pkg-link" href={`${base}/pkg/sdk-core/`}>{sdkCore.npm}</a>
      decides whether a fresh delegation request can be derived from
      what the session already holds.
    </p>

    <h2>a three-link chain, drawn</h2>

    <div class="mermaid-wrap" style="margin: 24px 0; height: 380px; position: relative;">
      <span class="cap">delegation-chain.svg</span>

      {chain.map((link, i) => (
        <div style={`position:absolute; top:${28 + i * 110}px; left:32px; right:32px;`}>
          <div class="row gap-12 middle">
            <span class="pin" style="position:relative;">{i + 1}</span>
            <div class="card" style="flex:1; padding: 10px 14px;">
              <div class="row between middle" style="margin-bottom: 4px;">
                <div class="mono" style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--ink);">{link.label}</div>
                <div class="row gap-6">
                  <span class="pill mono">space={link.space}</span>
                  <span class="pill mono">path={link.path}</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="row gap-6 wrap" style="margin-top: 4px;">
                {link.actions.map(a => <span class="pill kind-core mono">{a}</span>)}
              </div>
              <div class="label" style="margin-top: 8px; text-transform:none; letter-spacing: 0; font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: var(--ink-3);">{link.note}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}

      <!-- subset arrow on the right -->
      <svg style="position:absolute; top:40px; right:8px; width:24px; height:300px;">
        <defs>
          <marker id="ah-sub" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto">
            <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="var(--accent)" />
          </marker>
        </defs>
        <line x1="12" y1="0" x2="12" y2="290" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-dasharray="4 4" marker-end="url(#ah-sub)" />
      </svg>

      <div class="callout" style="top: 110px; right: 36px; transform: rotate(2deg); max-width: 160px;">
        each link ⊆ its parent. <br/>strictly. no exceptions.
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>what a capability is, exactly</h2>
    <p>
      A {sdkCore.npm} <code>PermissionEntry</code> is a four-tuple:
      service, space, path, and a set of action URNs. The service is the
      long-form namespace (<code>tinycloud.kv</code>, <code>tinycloud.sql</code>,
      <code>tinycloud.duckdb</code>, <code>tinycloud.capabilities</code>).
      The space is the storage container (a short name like
      <code>default</code> or a full <code>tinycloud:pkh:eip155:…:name</code>
      URI; the SDK normalizes both forms before comparing). The path is
      service-specific — a key prefix for KV, a database name for SQL.
      Actions are full URNs like <code>tinycloud.kv/get</code>.
    </p>

    <div class="card tinted" style="padding: 18px 20px; margin: 16px 0;">
      <div class="label" style="margin-bottom: 6px;">subset rules — verbatim from <code>capabilities.ts</code></div>
      <ul class="col gap-4" style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">
        <li><strong>service</strong> — exact match.</li>
        <li><strong>space</strong> — exact match after normalization (full URI vs short name collapse to the trailing segment).</li>
        <li><strong>path</strong> — if granted ends in <code>/</code> it's a prefix; otherwise it's exact.</li>
        <li><strong>actions</strong> — every URN in <code>requested.actions</code> must appear in <code>granted.actions</code>.</li>
        <li>any requested entry without a matching grant goes into <code>missing[]</code>; non-empty <code>missing</code> means non-subset, period.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>where the chain lives in code</h2>

    <div class="row gap-16" style="margin: 16px 0;">
      <a href={`${base}/pkg/sdk-rs/`} class="card" style="flex:1; padding: 14px 16px; text-decoration: none; color: var(--ink);">
        <div class="label">rust kernel</div>
        <div class="mono" style="margin: 4px 0; font-size: 13px;">{sdkRs.npm}</div>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 13px;">
          <code>createDelegation</code>, <code>useDelegation</code>,
          <code>parseRecapFromSiwe</code>. {sdkRs.modules} modules ·
          {sdkRs.loc.toLocaleString()} loc. Built on the
          <code>tinycloud_sdk_rs</code> auth crate (re-exported from
          tinycloud-node).
        </p>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/pkg/sdk-core/`} class="card" style="flex:1; padding: 14px 16px; text-decoration: none; color: var(--ink);">
        <div class="label">subset checker</div>
        <div class="mono" style="margin: 4px 0; font-size: 13px;">{sdkCore.npm}</div>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 13px;">
          <code>isCapabilitySubset</code>, <code>parseRecapCapabilities</code>,
          <code>DelegationManager</code>, <code>resolveManifest</code>.
          {sdkCore.modules} modules · {sdkCore.loc.toLocaleString()} loc.
          Decides whether a request needs a wallet prompt or can ride the
          existing session.
        </p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="row gap-16" style="margin: 16px 0;">
      <a href={`${base}/pkg/sdk-services/`} class="card" style="flex:1; padding: 14px 16px; text-decoration: none; color: var(--ink);">
        <div class="label">capability registry</div>
        <div class="mono" style="margin: 4px 0; font-size: 13px;">{services.npm}</div>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 13px;">
          {services.why} The registry tracks which key (session, ingested,
          ephemeral) holds which capabilities, with priority ordering so
          the right key is selected for each invocation.
        </p>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/pkg/node-sdk/`} class="card" style="flex:1; padding: 14px 16px; text-decoration: none; color: var(--ink);">
        <div class="label">authoring surface</div>
        <div class="mono" style="margin: 4px 0; font-size: 13px;">{nodeSdk.npm}</div>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 13px;">
          <code>createDelegation()</code> &amp; <code>delegateTo()</code>
          on <code>TinyCloudNode</code>. The node-side surface owns
          chain authoring; the wallet-prompt fallback only fires when the
          requested scope isn't already covered by the active session.
        </p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <h2>verifying a chain end-to-end</h2>
    <p>
      Verification happens in two places. The signing side
      (<code>createDelegation</code> in {sdkRs.npm}) checks that the
      proposed child entries are derivable from the parent SIWE's recap
      capabilities — if not, it refuses to sign. The serving side (the
      tinycloud node) re-runs the same subset check on every invocation
      against the proof the SDK ships in the <code>Authorization</code>
      header. Both sides use the same Rust crate, so there's no drift
      between what the SDK promises and what the node enforces.
    </p>

    <p>
      The fast path through <code>delegateTo</code> in {nodeSdk.npm}
      hands {sdkCore.npm}'s subset checker the parsed recap capabilities
      from the current session and the requested entries. Subset → it
      builds a UCAN over the session key (no wallet). Non-subset → it
      throws <code>PermissionNotInManifestError</code> with the missing
      entries, and the legacy wallet path takes over.
    </p>

    <div class="card" style="padding: 14px 16px; margin: 16px 0; border-color: var(--accent);">
      <div class="label" style="margin-bottom: 6px;">the silent rule</div>
      <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 14px;">
        <code>disableSubDelegation</code> in <code>createDelegation()</code>
        truncates the chain at the recipient. The recipient may
        <em>invoke</em> but cannot mint a child. Use this for credentials
        that should not propagate beyond a single trusted edge.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>data this chapter reads</h3>
    <ul class="col gap-4">
      <li class="mono">/atlas/data/inventory.json</li>
      <li class="mono">/atlas/data/pkg/sdk-core.json</li>
      <li class="mono">/atlas/data/pkg/sdk-rs.json</li>
      <li class="mono">/atlas/data/pkg/sdk-services.json</li>
      <li class="mono">/atlas/data/pkg/node-sdk.json</li>
      <li class="mono">/atlas/data/pkg/web-sdk.json</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>where to read next</h3>
    <p>
      Chapter <a class="pkg-link" href={`${base}/06/`}>06</a> takes a
      whole chain, packages it into a single shareable bundle, and walks
      through what a recipient can — and cannot — do with it.
    </p>
  </article>
</Atlas>
